<br>
Anyway, on to what I want to say...<br>
<br>
I quite agree with the people who said that paganistic beliefs seem to be the &quot;in&quot; thing to do these days.  I have known many people that go after some radical idea just for shock value and rebellion.  Overall I just don't care for people who do things just to stand out anyway.  But those here who stated those beliefs have given very good explanation behind them.  I can see through your posts that you're all not just following something blindly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Even one of my best friends claims that he is Atheist, merely because of lack of direction in his life.<br>
<br>
As for myself, I am quite agnostic, simply because my entire life, I have been extremely skeptical.  For the most part, if I don't see proof of something, it's not there.  These beliefs of mine spread even to extraterrestrials, and little brothers who destroy raids. <br>
<br>
EDIT: Yikes! The spell checker cut out a whole lot of stuff.  Here is all is again...<br>
<br>
Lately I have taken up studies of Taoism and Buddism.  These philosohies have given me a direction to get my life straightened out, stop worrying about dumb things, eat healthier and so forth.<br>
<br>
Blah...I'm not going to type all that crap again.  It was a rant about how I can't stand people who push their beleifs on others, and how much living in Georgia sucks, because every race/religion here hates one another.  Oh, and then a rant about how the main church in the town I work in controls the entire town.  They had the tobacco shop closed down, wont allow a liquor store, you can't buy a Playboy at a convenience store, or Barnes and Noble's even, and they even comes in and makes sure the comic shop is up to their standards.  So just imagine an intelligent rant about all that stuff. <p><center><img src="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/821180.jpg"  border="0"></center>
